        "text": "Some of the things that make Agile work include team collaboration across functions and an uninterrupted flow of work that cut across functional silos enabling continuous delivery of value to the customers, fast feedback loops, and fast learning.\n\nParadoxically forming an Agile Transformation Team or a team of Agile Coaches means creating even one more functional silo, where the alegged purpose of those same teams should be replacing functional silos with cross-functional teams and with product or service departments.\n\nInstead, change agents such as Transformation Leads and Agile Coaches should belong to and be embedded in the teams and departments they are supporting. They should be connected via a network and act in a federated way similar to the way Communities Of Practice work."
